ium of Puck=E2=80=99s
best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Dylan Byers chronicles the boardroom culture shift as blue =
chip advertisers, many of whom established a tactical distance from Fox New=
s in recent years, quietly return to the network=E2=80=94the latest data po=
int evidencing how C.E.O. Lachlan Murdoch is benefiting from a broader poli=
tical realignment.

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Leigh Ann Caldwell explores the liberation of Mitch M=
cConnell and its implications for the MAGA agenda. Bill Cohan envisions the=
 potential death of private equity=E2=80=99s favorite tax loophole. Marion =
Maneker combs through the auction numbers for New York=E2=80=99s Old Master=
 season. And Sarah Shapiro charts the ascent of =E2=80=9Cantidepressant fas=
hion.=E2=80=9D

Meanwhile, on the pods: NBC Sports president Rick Cordella joins John Ouran=
d on The Varsity to present a 30,000-foot view of the NFL=E2=80=99s media r=
ights negotiations. On Impolitic, John Heilemann rings up constitutional sc=
holar Laurence Tribe to discuss the challenge of guardrailing Trump=E2=80=
=99s sprawling agenda. And on The Powers That Be, Jon Kelly
reunites with Peter Hamby to dissect the administration=E2=80=99s decision =
to cut ties with several D.C. publications.

